                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.51 Et 3/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bading</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-17T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1923—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Your 20, December 13, 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>In reply to the President’s communication you will address a note to him stating
                    that the contents of his communication having been transmitted to the Department
                    you are directed by your Government to inform him that it has noted with
                    satisfaction his assurances that the Ecuadorean Government will always respect
                    and comply with its contracts.</p>
                <p>Should you learn definitely that the loan contract is to be signed you will
                    immediately request an interview with the President, or should he be absent from
                    Quito, with the Minister for Foreign Affairs, and inform him that this
                    Government will not view with favor the floating of such a loan in the United
                    States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
